00:55:18,108 --> 00:55:23,090
I feel like a lot of games are slowly becoming the live ops kind of model of things.

943
00:55:23,130 --> 00:55:26,772
And until you get to live ops, you just kind of keep going for it until you get there.

944
00:55:26,812 --> 00:55:28,213
So I'm just curious, right?

945
00:55:28,253 --> 00:55:31,874
You're well known for a lot of different games and expansions and sequels.

946
00:55:32,574 --> 00:55:33,795
Now we're in a live ops mode.

947
00:55:33,815 --> 00:55:36,876
Do you see that as like a future for the next decade or so?

948
00:55:37,777 --> 00:55:38,577
Yeah, I mean, I think.

949
00:55:39,783 --> 00:55:45,886
I think if you're trying to make a game that builds a community that sticks around,

950
00:55:46,426 --> 00:55:48,147
then I think it's worth thinking of it as a live service.

951
00:55:48,187 --> 00:55:49,328
Like no matter what type of game you're making.

952
00:55:49,368 --> 00:55:53,170
You could be making a rogue-like 8-bit indie game,

